Fix missing newline after Import-Name / Import-Namespace metadata fields.

flit_core 4.0.0 introduced the metadata 2.5 Import-Name and Import-Namespace
fields but writes them without a trailing newline, unlike every other field.
As a result the single newline that should separate the email headers from the
description body is consumed terminating the Import-Name line, leaving no blank
separator. Strict RFC 822 parsers (e.g. Syft, used for SBOM generation) then
read the first line of the description as a malformed header and fail with
"malformed header line: flit_core".

Upstream: https://github.com/pypa/flit

--- a/flit_core/flit_core/common.py
+++ b/flit_core/flit_core/common.py
@@ -444,10 +444,10 @@ class Metadata:
             fp.write(f'Provides-Extra: {normalised_extra}\n')
 
         for name in self.import_name:
-            fp.write(f'Import-Name: {name}')
+            fp.write(f'Import-Name: {name}\n')
 
         for name in self.import_namespace:
-            fp.write(f'Import-Namespace: {name}')
+            fp.write(f'Import-Namespace: {name}\n')
 
         if self.description is not None:
             fp.write(f'\n{self.description}\n')
